<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1495,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[198,274,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Tubes.</emphasis>
—Generative hyphae infrequent, hyaline, thin-walled, usually unbranched, 2.0–4.0 µm in diam; skeletal hyphae dominant, hyaline, thick-walled with a wide to narrow lumen, unbranched, interwoven, 3.0– 
<quantity box="[203,286,1572,1598]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 µm</quantity>
in diam. Cystidia absent, but fusoid cystidioles present, hyaline, thin-walled, 17–23 × 4.0–5.0 µm; basidia barrel-shaped, with four sterigmata and a basal clamp connection, 20–29 × 
<quantity box="[1155,1302,1611,1637]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.325" metricValueMax="1.55" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="13.25" valueMax="15.5" valueMin="11.0">11–15.5 µm</quantity>
; basidioles dominant, in shape similar to basidia, but slightly smaller.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1495,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis box="[198,310,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Spores.—</emphasis>
Basidiospores ellipsoid, truncate, hyaline, thick-walled, smooth, strongly dextrinoid, CB+, (16–)16.5–19.5(–20) × (7.5–)8.0–9.5(–10) µm, L = 
<quantity box="[758,859,1727,1753]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8199999999999998" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="18.2">18.2 µm</quantity>
, W = 
<quantity box="[930,1031,1727,1753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.67" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="8.67">8.67 µm</quantity>
, Q = 2.07–2.11 (n = 60/2).
</paragraph>
